[Prune Help]

prune <amount> - Prunes messages

Options:
    [--bots] - Prunes all messages created by any bot
    [--user <search>] - Prunes all messages by the specified user

    [--filter <filter>] - Only prunes messages that contain the specified string

    [--attachments | -a] - Only prunes messages containing attachments (can be combined with --embeds)
    [--embeds | -e] - Only prunes messages containing embeds (can be combined with --attachments)
    [--pinned | -p] - Also prunes pinned messages (they are not pruned by default)
    [--invites | -i] - Only prunes messages containing discord invites

Flags:
    [-s] - Silent. I don't tell you shit after

Examples:
    prune 10
    prune 10 -aes
    prune 10 -s --filter hello

<> = required information, []= optional information, | = or, Don't include <> [] or | in you command input or else you are a fucking dipshit
Annoy everyone in the support if you are too lazy to check the docs (=support for link)```

help.role.full:
```css
[Role Help]

role give <role[,role...]> - Gives roles
role take <role[,role...]> - Takes roles
role modify <role> - Modifies a role

Aliases:
    giverole, takerole, modifyrole

Options for role give and role take:
    [--bots] - Will only change roles for bots
    [--users] - Will only change roles for users
    [--user <user[,user...]>] - Will only change roles for specified users

    [--inrole <role>] - Will only change roles if the target has the specified role
    [--notinrole <role>] - Will only change roles if the target doesn't have the specified role
    [--noroles] - Will only change roles if the target doesn't have any roles

Options for role modify:
    [--name <name>] - rename the role
    [--color <color>] - Changes the color of a role
    [--move-after <role>] - Set role position after target role

Examples:
    role give Admin, Mod --user TheAkio
    giverole Bot --inrole Bot
    takerole Muted --user HcgRandon, TheAkio
    role modify Bad --color #FF0000
    modifyrole Admin --color blue

Note:
    This command will not allow you to give, take or modify roles that are in a higher position than your highest role!

<> = required information, []= optional information, | = or, do not include <> [] or | in you command input
Please join the support server for any questions. (=support for link)```
help.sar.full:

[Self Assignable Roles (SAR) Help]

sar | sar help - Shows this help message
sar create <group> - Creates a SAR group
sar delete <group> - Deletes a SAR group
sar rename <group> <new name> - Renames a SAR group
sar groups - List all groups

Group modification:
    sar <group> active <bool> - Activates or deactivates this group
    sar <group> reqrole <role> - Sets the role that a user needs to have to use this group
    sar <group> max <number> - Sets the max amount of roles a user can have from this group
    sar <group> roles add <role[,role...]> - Adds roles to this group
    sar <group> roles remove <role[,role...]> - Removes roles from this group
    sar <group> default - Sets or unsets this group as the default one

Examples:
    sar create colors
    sar colors default
    sar colors roles add Red, Green, Blue
    sar colors max 1
    sar colors active false

Note:
    To use the assignment interface you need to use {{prefix}}rank [group]

<> = required information, []= optional information, | = or, do not include <> [] or | in you command input
Please join the support server for any questions. ({{prefix}}support for link)```
